This paper deals with a messaging system that provides cryptographic privacy, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the scalability of the system, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The system uses multiple servers to support more users, which is a topic related to computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of mix networks, which are commonly used in the field of cryptography (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the latency of the system, which is a topic related to systems and information theory (cs.SI).
